sql:
SELECT DISTINCT vehicle_id
FROM performance_metrics
WHERE consistency_pct < 70 AND no_info_instances > 10;

external_knowledge:
- "More than 10 times" implies high access counts; ; 
- The query assumes that vehicles are analyzed periodically, and their performance metrics, such as fuel efficiency, can change over time; ; 
- Driving experience is considered an important factor in vehicle performance and maintenance needs; ; 
- User access counts are used as a measure of system activity or engagement; ; 
- The system tracks maintenance history to monitor vehicle health and plan for future maintenance.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT vehicle_id
FROM vehicle_history
WHERE status = 'inactive';

external_knowledge:
- The user hierarchy is assumed to start with users who did not change any vehicle status (i.e., they are at the top level); 
- Severity score is calculated based on the alert severity: High=3, Medium=2, Low=1; 
- The latest maintenance alert per vehicle is considered based on the most recent alert date; 
- The current status of each vehicle is the latest status update based on the change date.
